                   and many downstream applications. Recently one-stage methods
                   have gained much attention over two-stage approaches due to
                   their simpler design and competitive performance. Here we
                   propose a fully convolutional one-stage object detector
                   (FCOS) to solve object detection in a per-pixel prediction
                   fashion, analogue to other dense prediction problems such as
                   semantic segmentation. Almost all state-of-the-art object
                   detectors such as RetinaNet, SSD, YOLOv3, and Faster R-CNN
                   rely on pre-defined anchor boxes. In contrast, our proposed
                   detector FCOS is anchor box free, as well as proposal free.
                   By eliminating the pre-defined set of anchor boxes, FCOS
                   completely avoids the complicated computation related to
